    projects:
    - name: "Job Automation Suite"
      date: 2026-02 – Present
      summary: "Architected an open-source automation platform (**2,000+ clones**) that unifies disparate data scraping and document rendering engines into a centralized web application powered by **Python**, **Streamlit**, and **Docker**."
      highlights:
      - "Unified two complex, terminal-based applications into a cohesive monorepo architecture, engineering an intuitive frontend command center using **Python** and **Streamlit** that achieved widespread open-source adoption with over **2,000+** repository clones."
      - "Engineered an asynchronous web scraping and data ingestion pipeline capable of harvesting and standardizing **1,500+** unstructured web records daily, implementing robust error handling to guarantee continuous uptime and zero rate-limiting interruptions."
      - "Developed a sophisticated data analytics engine utilizing **Pandas** to execute complex keyword-matching algorithms, automatically parsing unstructured text datasets to isolate, score, and rank the top **5%** most highly correlated records."
      - "Architected an autonomous document generation pipeline integrating **LLM orchestration** with **ruamel.yaml** for AST-based (Abstract Syntax Tree) data mutation, dynamically compiling outputs via **RenderCV** while guaranteeing **100%** structural data integrity."
      - "Containerized the entire multi-service application suite utilizing **Docker Compose** to establish a resilient, cross-platform deployment environment with continuous data synchronization, reducing end-to-end processing time from **45** minutes to under **2** minutes."
      - "**[GitHub Repository](https://github.com/johndoe/job-automation-suite)**"
    - name: AI Agentic Suite (Workflow Optimization)
      date: 2026-01 – Present
      summary: A highly optimized, multi-agent framework configured to
        drastically accelerate personal software engineering and research
        lifecycles.
      highlights:
      - Customized an agentic architecture to act as a virtual engineering
        department, transitioning personal workflow into a managerial role
        orchestrating a specialized team of AI "experts."
      - Engineered parallel execution branches to automate code generation,
        deep-dive research, and daily reporting, achieving a **10x** increase in
        personal shipping velocity.
      - Optimized the agentic suite to mimic the rapid iteration cycles of elite
        AI labs, freeing up cognitive bandwidth to focus strictly on high-level
        systems architecture and strategic problem-solving.
    - name: "Exam Proctoring Platform"
      date: 2025-10 – Present
      summary: "Architected an open-source, full-stack proctoring platform designed to secure academic testing environments through real-time telemetry, spatial mapping, and dynamic classroom administration. Tech Stack: **React (TS)**, **FastAPI**, **MySQL**, **Docker**, **Linux**, **Bash**, **Ansible**, **SSH**, **LDAP**."
      highlights:
      - "Engineered a highly concurrent, full-stack architecture utilizing **React (TypeScript)** and an asynchronous **FastAPI (Python)** backend, leveraging **MySQL** connection pooling to sustain sub-**50ms** API response times."
      - "Automated the mass physical imaging and bare-metal provisioning of **40+** workstations by engineering a suite of custom **Bash** scripts and **Ansible** playbooks, reducing hardware deployment time by **85%**."
      - "Architected a standardized, remote **Linux** development environment utilizing secure **SSH** configurations, and containerized the application deployment pipeline via **Docker** to guarantee **100%** environment parity."
      - "Implemented strict enterprise-grade security protocols by integrating **LDAP** for institutional identity verification and engineering a comprehensive **RBAC** system, enforcing session exclusivity across **500+** university accounts."
      - "Designed a fault-tolerant, atomic file submission engine integrating **Webhooks**, capable of processing bulk **CSV** user imports and asynchronous **Zip** payload streaming for **1,000+** assignments with zero data loss."
      - "Developed a responsive, real-time instructor dashboard featuring a spatial room mapping system built with **CSS Modules**, providing granular telemetry on student connectivity and upload progress for **150+** concurrent users."
      - "**[GitHub Repository](https://github.com/johndoe/exam-proctoring)**"
    - name: AI-Powered Content Pipeline
      date: 2025
      summary: Fully automated system for generating and posting short-form
